A rather quaint designation for a place that bears the indelible stain of history, [Rich Hill](/Rich_Hill) is more than just a structure; it's a silent witness to a pivotal, desperate moment in American history. Located discreetly northeast of [Bel Alton](/Bel_Alton,_Maryland) on Bel Alton-Newtown Road, this historic residence in [Maryland](/Maryland) holds a particular significance that transcends its architectural merits, placing it squarely within the tumultuous narrative of the [American Civil War](/American_Civil_War) and its immediate, violent aftermath.

